    {
      "id": "58e58318-7ac6-4b4e-8905-e4de1e86e310",
      "type": "description",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Soit $n \\in \\Nn^*$ fix\\'e et ${\\Delta} : {\\Rr_n [X]} \\mapsto {\\Rr_n [X]}$, ${P (X)} \\mapsto {P (X + 1)\n-P (X)}$.",
        "html": "<p>Soit <span class=\"math inline\">\\(n \\in \\Nn^*\\)</span> fixé et <span class=\"math inline\">\\({\\Delta} : {\\Rr_n [X]} \\mapsto {\\Rr_n [X]}\\)</span>, <span class=\"math inline\">\\({P (X)} \\mapsto {P (X + 1)\n-P (X)}\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "12961764-fa92-4cb6-be36-d20811a734e0",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Montrer que $\\Delta$ est lin\\'eaire, i.e. que $\\forall (a, b) \\in \\Rr^2$ et\n$ (P, Q) \\in \\Rr_n [X] \\, \\, \\Delta (aP  + bQ) = a\\Delta (P) + b\\Delta (Q)$.",
        "html": "<p>Montrer que <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\Delta\\)</span> est linéaire, i.e. que <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\forall (a, b) \\in \\Rr^2\\)</span> et <span class=\"math inline\">\\((P, Q) \\in \\Rr_n [X] \\, \\, \\Delta (aP  + bQ) = a\\Delta (P) + b\\Delta (Q)\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "e8c5b140-621b-4a58-bd54-29a3419f9784",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "D\\'eterminer $\\ker (\\Delta) = \\left\\{ P \\in \\Rr_n[X] / \\Delta (P) = 0\\right\\}$.",
        "html": "<p>Déterminer <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\ker (\\Delta) = \\left\\{ P \\in \\Rr_n[X] / \\Delta (P) = 0\\right\\}\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "ce3c7f82-15b6-478a-9a5e-4ef783a5c7a9",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Soient $H_0 = 1$ et pour $k \\in \\left\\{ 1, \\ldots, n\\right\\} \\, \\,\nH_k = \\dfrac 1{k ! } X (X-1)\\ldots (X-k + 1)$. Calculer $\\Delta (H_k)$.",
        "html": "<p>Soient <span class=\"math inline\">\\(H_0 = 1\\)</span> et pour <span class=\"math inline\">\\(k \\in \\left\\{ 1, \\ldots, n\\right\\} \\, \\,\nH_k = \\dfrac 1{k ! } X (X-1)\\ldots (X-k + 1)\\)</span>. Calculer <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\Delta (H_k)\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "887e869d-6e43-481d-a82a-4fc44460db46",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Soit $Q \\in \\Rr_{n-1}[X]$. Comment trouver $P \\in \\Rr_{n}[X]$ tel que\n$\\Delta (P) = Q$. ",
        "html": "<p>Soit <span class=\"math inline\">\\(Q \\in \\Rr_{n-1}[X]\\)</span>. Comment trouver <span class=\"math inline\">\\(P \\in \\Rr_{n}[X]\\)</span> tel que <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\Delta (P) = Q\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "b99de0de-bd76-4179-920e-ee66cf323193",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "D\\'eterminer $P$ pour $Q = X^2$ tel que $P (1) = 0$.",
        "html": "<p>Déterminer <span class=\"math inline\">\\(P\\)</span> pour <span class=\"math inline\">\\(Q = X^2\\)</span> tel que <span class=\"math inline\">\\(P (1) = 0\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
